Before the 40th anniversary of "LIVE" the legendary rock band can be introduced at an exhibition in Liepaja.
The exhibition will explore various 'Lives' items, photographs that are reproduced in a timeline to reflect the group's activities from the earliest days until 2010, when the group's activities are announced to be over.
The exhibition will also feature costumes, musical instruments, awards and recordings, as well as other unseen items from the creative work of the group "Līvi".
The exhibition will be supplemented by items from the collection of the Museum of Lichtenstein.
The visual design of the exhibition was created in collaboration with the fashion artist and painter Elita Patmalnić.
Musicians associated with the group "LIVE" and their relatives also responded to the invitation and shared objects and memories.
The origins of "Liv" can be traced back to 1972, when a vocal instrumental ensemble was formed in the House of Culture in Liepāja, led by Juris Pavitolas.
The ensemble participated in the festival "Liepaja zintar" in 1972 and 1974, as well as in the city and republican shows.
In 1976, the fateful meeting took place when Juris Pavitola met Erik Kigeli and formed a group at the Metalurgic Palace of Culture, inviting Ingrid Gutman, Andri Krūzinis and Jāni Groduma to join.
Over the years, the group's composition has changed several times.
Members have joined, others have gone their way, some have returned.
However, the main thing - the desire to prove that Latvian rock music is capable of living and existing - has remained unchanged.
"There was no shortage of jeans, mattresses, and barbells, and these boys were a marked departure from the stereotype of the stage", says music critic Klaus Wawere.
Besides the aforementioned musicians, the group included such fine musicians as Igor, Vilnis Rosiņš, Modris Stern, Valdis Stark, Laimas Răcenăi, Talius Pusbarnieks, Ainar Virga, Aivars Brizis, Guntars Mucenieks, Dainis Virga, Tomass Klein, and many others.
Admission to the exhibition is free.
The exhibition runs from 19 August to 30 October.
On August 27, the 40th anniversary of the group "Līvi" will be celebrated in the "Pūt, vējiņi" concert hall in the city of Liège.
